  1. Oxford 3000
  2. Oxford 11

Words 1001-1100

  1. fascinating
    The book about space was absolutely fascinating.

  2. fashion
    She has a great sense of fashion and always looks stylish.

  3. fashionable
    Wearing hats has become fashionable again this year.

  4. fast
    The car was moving so fast that it was hard to see it clearly.

  5. fasten
    Please fasten your seatbelt before the plane takes off.

  6. fat
    The cat became fat because it ate too much food.

  7. father
    My father taught me how to ride a bicycle.

  8. fault
    It was not her fault that the meeting was delayed.

  9. favour
    Could you do me a favour and help me carry this box?

  10. favourite
    Pizza is my favourite food to eat on weekends.

  11. fear
    He has a fear of heights and avoids tall buildings.

  12. feather
    The bird dropped a beautiful feather on the ground.

  13. feature
    The main feature of the phone is its high-quality camera.

  14. February
    My birthday is in February, the shortest month of the year.

  15. fee
    There is a small fee to enter the museum.

  16. feed
    We need to feed the dog before we leave the house.

  17. feedback
    The teacher gave us feedback on our essays.

  18. feel
    I feel happy when I spend time with my friends.

  19. feeling
    She had a strange feeling that someone was watching her.

  20. fellow
    He is a fellow student in my math class.

  21. female
    The female bird is smaller than the male bird.

  22. fence
    They built a fence around the garden to keep animals out.

  23. festival
    The music festival attracted people from all over the country.

  24. few
    Only a few people came to the meeting today.

  25. fiction
    She enjoys reading fiction books about magical worlds.

  26. field
    The children played football in the large field.

  27. fifteen
    There are fifteen apples in the basket.

  28. fifth
    She finished the race in fifth place.

  29. fifty
    The box weighs fifty kilograms and is very heavy.

  30. fight
    The two boys had a fight over the last piece of cake.

  31. fighting
    The soldiers were tired after a long day of fighting.

  32. figure
    She drew a figure of a man on the whiteboard.

  33. file
    Please save the document as a PDF file.

  34. fill
    Can you fill this bottle with water for me?

  35. film
    We watched an interesting film about wildlife last night.

  36. final
    The final exam will take place next week.

  37. finally
    After hours of searching, they finally found the missing keys.

  38. finance
    He decided to study finance at university.

  39. financial
    The company is facing financial difficulties this year.

  40. find
    I need to find my glasses before I can read the book.

  41. finding
    The finding of the study surprised many scientists.

  42. fine
    The weather was fine, so we decided to go for a walk.

  43. finger
    She cut her finger while chopping vegetables.

  44. finish
    I need to finish my homework before dinner.

  45. fire
    The fire in the fireplace kept the room warm.

  46. firm
    He gave me a firm handshake when we met.

  47. first
    She was the first person to arrive at the party.

  48. firstly
    Firstly, we need to gather all the necessary materials.

  49. fish
    We saw a colorful fish swimming in the clear water.

  50. fishing
    They went fishing by the lake early in the morning.

  51. fit
    These shoes fit me perfectly and are very comfortable.

  52. fitness
    Regular exercise is important for maintaining fitness.

  53. five
    There are five chairs around the dining table.

  54. fix
    Can you help me fix the broken chair?

  55. fixed
    The plumber fixed the leaking pipe in the kitchen.

  56. flag
    The national flag was raised during the ceremony.

  57. flame
    The candle’s flame flickered in the wind.

  58. flash
    There was a flash of lightning during the storm.

  59. flat
    The road was completely flat and easy to walk on.

  60. flexible
    This material is flexible and can bend without breaking.

  61. flight
    Our flight to Paris was delayed by two hours.

  62. float
    The boat began to float gently on the calm water.

  63. flood
    The heavy rain caused a flood in the city.

  64. floor
    She cleaned the floor until it was shiny and spotless.

  65. flour
    We need more flour to bake the cake.

  66. flow
    The river’s flow was strong after the recent rain.

  67. flower
    A beautiful flower bloomed in the garden this morning.

  68. flu
    He stayed home from work because he had the flu.

  69. fly
    Birds fly south for the winter to find warmer weather.

  70. flying
    Flying in an airplane for the first time was exciting.

  71. focus
    You need to focus on your studies to do well in school.

  72. fold
    Please fold the clothes and put them in the drawer.

  73. folding
    She bought a folding chair for the camping trip.

  74. folk
    Folk music is popular in many rural areas.

  75. follow
    Please follow the instructions carefully to complete the task.

  76. following
    The following day, they decided to visit the museum.

  77. food
    The restaurant serves delicious food at a reasonable price.

  78. foot
    He injured his foot while playing football.

  79. football
    They watched a football match on television last night.

  80. for
    This gift is for you as a token of appreciation.

  81. force
    The wind was strong enough to force the door open.

  82. foreign
    She enjoys learning about foreign cultures and traditions.

  83. forest
    They went hiking in the forest to enjoy the fresh air.

  84. forever
    I will remember this day forever.

  85. forget
    Don’t forget to bring your umbrella; it might rain later.

  86. forgive
    She decided to forgive him for his mistake.

  87. fork
    He used a fork to eat the salad.

  88. form
    Please fill out this form before the interview.

  89. formal
    The event requires formal attire, so wear a suit.

  90. former
    She is a former employee of the company.

  91. fortunately
    Fortunately, no one was hurt in the accident.

  92. fortune
    He made a fortune by investing in real estate.

  93. forty
    There are forty students in our class this year.

  94. forward
    She took a step forward to get a better view.

  95. found
    I found my lost keys under the sofa.

  96. four
    There are four seasons in a year.

  97. fourteen
    She turned fourteen years old last week.

  98. fourth
    He finished the race in fourth place.

  99. frame
    The picture looks beautiful in that wooden frame.

  100. free
    The museum offers free admission on Sundays.
